Monks do far more than 20% over warriors.  Just like Rogues do far more than the &quot;intende&quot; 40% over warriors.<br>
<br>
Monks to closer to 50% and rouges 100% more damamge... check logs and parses... <br>
<br>
In any situation where you are not needing constant cheal chains the monk is a better tank.. they take less damage... they can instant self heal.. warriors are MT's because of defensive, nothing more... <br>
<br>
Monks, today, are bar none the best meele class in the game, it's not even a contest.. not just high level but from the ground up.. the defensive changes won't affect the top end monks on a raiding level.. not really.. oh you might need to know what you are doing now, but I don't see anything you used to do reliably be unable to do now, pullingwise or rolewise.<br>
<br>
What it *will* effect in a major way (if the changes are as drastic as some folks are saying) is soloing.  More downtime on killing blues.  Someone made a (intended to be) serious bemaon that he'd need buffs to solo well now.   Welcome to the world of other meeles.  <br>
<br>
I don't think this change was so drastically needed tho...and any time you do a straight nerf to a class on something that has been around for so long it sucks for that class, no matter how well-thought out and balanced it may or may not be. <p>Gurunt Bangoo <Wraith>
